  "about.title": {
    "other": "Minust"
  },
  "about.description": {
    "other": "Lugu sellest, kes ma olen, kust ma tulen, mis on mu kirg ja mille poole ma püüdlen."
  },
  "about.chapters.6.title": {
    "other": "ma tahtsin veel midagi öelda"
  },
  "about.chapters.6.content1": {
    "other": "so here's the part they weren't supposed to read."
  },
  "about.chapters.6.content2": {
    "other": "i'm still angry. still grieving a version of myself that was never allowed to exist. still waking up some days wondering why everything feels a few degrees off. sometimes i think about running away, just disappearing, new name, new city, new language. sometimes i almost do it."
  },
  "about.chapters.6.content3": {
    "other": "there are days i don't even feel human. more like a memory trying to solidify. more like an echo of something softer i can't reach anymore. other days, i'm electric. i feel every detail, sunlight on skin, quiet playlists, the way people's faces shift when they're finally safe enough to be themselves. it keeps me alive, somehow."
  },
  "about.chapters.6.content4": {
    "other": "i'm not done becoming whoever the hell i'm supposed to be. but i am done pretending that i'm okay with staying silent."
  },
